                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2865.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-26T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department’s February 20, 6 p.m., referred to in your February 21, 5 p.m.,
                    contemplated American citizens, that is, men as well as women and children.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
